Method and system for secure electronic communications over an insecure network
A method and system for providing secure electronic transactions over an insecure network such as the internet. The system allows a user to establish a secure link with a remote server and to transmit sensitive information while ensuring that the information is encrypted and that the user's identity is authenticated. The system uses a variety of security protocols, including SSL/TLS and IPsec, to provide secure communication.
1. A method of encrypting data transmitted between a computer comprising a processor and a memory and a remote server over an insecure network, said method comprising the steps of:
receiving at said processor of said computer a request to transmit data to said remote server;
generating a secret value using said processor of said computer;
encrypting said data using said secret value; and
transmitting said encrypted data from said computer to said remote server over said insecure network.
2. A method of authenticating a user over an insecure network, said method comprising the steps of:
receiving at a remote system over said insecure network a request from a user to access a resource;
generating a first token containing an encrypted version of a user identification value;
sending said first token to a client system associated with said user over said insecure network;
generating a second token containing a value of a one-time password (OTP) and a random value;
sending said second token to a client system associated with said user over said insecure network;
